                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, March 17 (PTI): The Supreme Court today directed the Central Adoption Resource Agency to consider as a one-time measure the plea of a German couple who want to adopt twins born through a surrogate Indian mother.           
	The apex court granted four weeks to the agency to explore the possibility to help the couple on humanitarian grounds. Surrogacy is a punishable offence in Germany. The couple had pleaded that if they were allowed inter-country adoption then the twins would get Indian passports, using which they could enter Germany.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court has held that Hyderabad, which is grappling with the Telangana agitation, would be a free zone entitling people from other parts of the state to compete for police and certain other government           jobs.                   
	 London (PTI): An illegal immigrant from India who carried out a frenzied knife attack on his former girlfriend in London in July 2008 was found guilty of murder on Wednesday and given a life sentence. Vikramjit Singh, 25, stabbed Gemma Dorman, 24, outside a Thai restaurant in southwest London where she was having dinner with her fianc.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): A bus caught fire because of a CNG leak around 7.25am on Wednesday near Paharganj in central Delhi. The 25-odd passengers had a narrow escape as the driver alerted them to get off and turned off the CNG system immediately.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Uttar Pradesh reported 61 child sex abuse cases in 2007 and 900 child rapes in 2008, the highest in the country. The figures have been given by the National Commission for Protection of Child Rights.                  
	 Bhopal (PTI): Three persons including an elderly woman lost sight in one eye allegedly after an operation at a free eye camp in Mandideep in Bhopal, sources said.                                                                                                                                              
